resources

Here is a list of things which I find useful and intend to find useful in the future. A lot of these are video links as I somehow learn faster from them. Included at the bottom is a list of people I find interesting and tend to look up to. I am by no means an expert in any of these fields, so if you have any suggestions, let me know!


Learning Resources

Control Lectures

  • Control Bootcamp by Steve Brunton

  • Control Theory Lectures by Christopher Lum, Boeing.

Kalman Filters

  • ilectureonline by Michel van Biezen. How the whole concept first clicked in my head.
  • Matlab tutorials.
  • SLAM course - WS13/14 by Prof. Cyrill Stachniss, University of Bonn. Literal gold.

Machine Learning

  • Machine Learning by Andrew Ng, Stanford University.

  • Machine Learning w/ Pytorch from Udemy.

  • How to Improve Deep Learning Performance from Machine Learning Mastery, a long list of things to try to help models learn faster.

Flight Mechanics

  • Flight Mechanics Course by Christopher Lum, Boeing.

Math

  • Algebra, Topology, Differential Calculus, and Optimization Theory For Computer Science and Machine Learning by UPenn. Basically a math dictionary for engineering or computer science.

Code

  • HTML & Javascript Tutorials by freecodecamp.

  • 4 Hour Long Crash Course for Python, No Ads by freecodecamp.


Profiles

  • Keifer Lee. A course mate I really look up to.
  • Phang Swee King. A friend who’s supposed to be my supervisor.
  • Felicia Wong. Super sweet lecturer from Taylor’s University.
